<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="assign-properties-to-group">6.4.2. Assigning properties to a group</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>plentymarkets includes a function, which you can use to simultaneously assign multiple properties to a group.</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Configuration</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the properties (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-check-square  "></i></span>) that you want to assign to the group.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Link groups</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="material-link"></i></span>).<br>
→ The <strong>Link groups</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select one or more property groups (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-check-square  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Link</strong>.<br>
→ The selected properties will be assigned to the groups.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="search-for-groups">6.4.3. Searching for existing groups</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Previously created property groups are displayed in an overview.</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Groups</strong>.</p>
<div class="olist loweralpha">
<ol class="loweralpha" type="a">
<li>
<p><strong><em>Option 1</em></strong>: Click on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-search  "></i></span> to see a list of all the groups.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Option 2</em></strong>: Click on <span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-filter  "></i></span> to narrow down the search results with filters.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on a group in the search results to open a detailed view.
There you can modify the group’s settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
